# P12-001 implementation plan (branch `feature/P12-001-remote-vfs-pgen-reads`)

Authoritative build plan for remote/VFS `.pgen` reads. Design rationale is in
`P12-001-remote-vfs-pgen-reads`; this is the how. **Milestone 1 (surface
enumeration) is done** ÔÇö result below. **Milestone 3 (the range-read spike) is the
go/no-go** for the full remote path; do not polish the patch set before that number.

## Architecture ÔÇö two I/O paths + a resolution front-end

Separate **path resolution** (glob / `pathmacro:` / `file_search_path` / protocol Ôćĺ
a concrete path) from **byte I/O** (how the bytes are pulled). Resolution is a VFS
front-end that runs for every input; I/O then takes one of two branches:

- **Path L ÔÇö native/local fastpath.** `PgenFile.ff` is a raw `FILE*` (`fopen` /
  `fread_unlocked`), **byte-identical to unpatched plink2**, stdio-buffered. Serves
  BOTH (a) plain-local paths [today's behavior] and (b) paths the VFS front-end
  resolved to a **local** file [the folded-in `file_search_path`/`pathmacro:` gap].
  No per-read VFS overhead.
- **Path V ÔÇö full VFS.** `PgenFile.vfs_handle` is a DuckDB `FileHandle`; the op
  wrappers use positioned `Read(buf, n, location)`. Serves **remote** paths
  (`s3://`, `https://`, ÔÇŽ) that can't be localized. Buffering comes from
  `cache_httpfs` (or an optional block layer), never from stdio.

"plink2-native" and "local-after-resolution" are the **same L branch**, differing
only in whether the front-end had to resolve the path. The two *paths* are L and V.

### `plinking_pgen_io` policy (explicit control; default auto)

| value | behavior |
|---|---|
| `auto` *(default)* | resolve via VFS; local Ôćĺ **L**, remote Ôćĺ **V** |
| `native` | raw `fopen` only, **no VFS at all** (pristine plink2; errors on a remote/unresolvable path) ÔÇö the zero-overhead / escape-hatch guarantee |
| `localize` | resolve, and **download remote Ôćĺ local temp**, then **L** (never per-read VFS; the safe, no-fork-needed remote strategy + the spike baseline) |
| `vfs` | always **V** (positioned reads even for local) ÔÇö for testing/consistency and measuring V overhead |

`auto` gives the good default; `native` guarantees today's behavior is untouched;
`localize` is what we ship if the spike says range-reads don't win; `vfs` is the
measurement/edge mode.

### The seam ÔÇö `fopencookie` (CHOSEN), not a struct/wrapper conversion

The milestone-1 enumeration proved the op set touching the file is **pure stdio**
(`fopen`/`fseeko`/`ftello`/`fread_unlocked`/`rewind`/`fclose`). That means a real
`FILE*` backed by custom callbacks ÔÇö glibc/musl **`fopencookie`** (macOS/BSD
**`funopen`**) ÔÇö is transparent to pgenlib: all reads/seeks/tells/closes work
**unchanged**. Verified: a cookie stream over positioned reads passes every one of
pgenlib's ops (SEEK_END/SET, `ftello`, `rewind`, `fread_unlocked`).

So the pgenlib patch is **just the 3 `fopen` sites** (L708 `shared_ff`, L824
`pgi_ff`, L2067 reader `ff`) redirected to `plinking_pgen_fopen(fname)`:

- **Path L (local/native):** `plinking_pgen_fopen` Ôćĺ real `fopen(fname, "rb")`.
  Byte-identical to unpatched plink2, stdio-buffered. The default.
- **Path V (VFS):** the extension (which has the `ClientContext`) opens a DuckDB
  `FileHandle` via `fs.OpenFile(path, READ, ClientContextFileOpener(context))` ÔÇö
  opener carries `SecretManager` Ôćĺ httpfs credentials + settings (file_system.hpp:149,
  file_opener.hpp:45) ÔÇö and registers a per-thread VFS opener. `plinking_pgen_fopen`
  then returns a **`fopencookie` `FILE*`** whose read/seek/close callbacks drive that
  `FileHandle` (positioned `Read(buf, n, location)`). glibc stdio **buffers the
  cookie stream**, so Path V gets readahead for free on top of the handle (and
  `cache_httpfs` under that).

pgenlib sees only `FILE*` on both paths Ôćĺ **no DuckDB types, no context, no struct
conversion, no fixpoint.** The 34 field-touch sites and their local `FILE*` copies
are all untouched. This is why the poison enumeration still mattered: it *proved*
the op set is stdio-only, which is exactly what makes the cookie transparent.

The two I/O paths are now: **real-`fopen` `FILE*`** (L) vs **cookie `FILE*`** (V) ÔÇö
pgenlib is agnostic. Extension picks L vs V at open via `IsRemoteFile`/`OnDiskFile`
and the `plinking_pgen_io` policy.

## Milestone 1 RESULT ÔÇö poison enumeration (done)

Poisoned the 3 read-path `FILE*` fields (`PoisonPgenFile*`) and compiled
`pgenlib_read.cc` in isolation with the CMake pgenlib flags. **34 error sites, all
in `pgenlib_read.cc`** ÔÇö completeness proven by the compiler. Op vocabulary = 5:

| op | sites |
|---|---|
| open (`fopen` + assign a `FILE*` into the field) | 3 (L2067 `pgrp->ff = fopen(...)`, L709/825) |
| `fseeko` | 9 |
| `ftello` | 2 |
| `fread_unlocked` | 2 |
| `fclose_null(&field)` (pgenlib helper, `FILE**`) | 5 |
| read field into a local `FILE*` (the local + its uses convert too) | 3 |

`getc_unlocked` / `rewind` don't touch these fields (block buffer, not file). State
carrier: `PgenFile { FILE* ff; void* vfs_handle; uint64_t vfs_off; }`; the 5 op
wrappers branch on `vfs_handle != nullptr`.

## Sequenced milestones

1. **Enumerate (done).** 34 field-touch sites / 5 ops, all pure stdio Ôćĺ cookie is
   transparent. This is what made the tiny-patch approach possible.
2. **2a ÔÇö shim scaffold + fopen redirect (local-transparent).** Add
   `plinking_pgen_fopen` (declared in a small header included by pgenlib; defined in
   `src/`, resolved at final `.so` link since pgenlib is a static lib). Default =
   real `fopen`. Redirect the 3 pgenlib `fopen` sites. Build; **full suite green** =
   byte-identical local. Tiny, safe first patch to the plink files.
3. **2b ÔÇö cookie + Path V (testable locally!).** Implement the `fopencookie` /
   `funopen` wrapper + a per-thread VFS-opener registration; extension opens the
   `FileHandle` with context and registers it. Add the `plinking_pgen_io` policy +
   `IsRemoteFile`/`OnDiskFile` selection + the `localize` strategy. **Test with no
   network**: back a cookie with a *local* file's positioned reads (or a
   LocalFileSystem `FileHandle`) and assert genotypes byte-identical to Path L ÔÇö
   this validates the entire VFS-read mechanism locally.
4. **3 ÔÇö MEASURE (go/no-go).** Contiguous-region query, bytes fetched + wall clock,
   over a local HTTP server: V raw httpfs vs V + `cache_httpfs` vs `localize`
   (download-to-temp). If V doesn't **decisively** beat `localize`, ship `localize`
   and keep V behind the flag. Only then invest in range-coalescing/`.pgi`/canary.

## Patch mechanism

Edits live as **re-appliable patches** to the `third_party/plink-ng` submodule
(`patches/plink-ng/*.patch`), applied idempotently at build time (precedent:
`src/musl_compat.h` force-included via CMake). Must be idempotent + CI-reproducible
from clean; minimal + one-logical-change-per-patch so they are **upstreamable**
(the `plink2_text.h:137` "network support later" comment is the open door). The
drift canary (`scripts/check_vendored_drift.sh`) treats the patch as the intended
delta. *(2a may edit the submodule directly to prove the patch, then capture as
`.patch` + CMake apply once green.)*

